==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bromine
<hw>Bro"mine</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ bad smell,
stink. Cf. <er>Brome</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>One of the
halogen elements, related in its chemical qualities to chlorine and
iodine. Atomic weight 79.8. Symbol Br. It is a deep reddish brown liquid
of a very disagreeable odor, emitting a brownish vapor at the ordinary
temperature. In combination it is found in minute quantities in sea
water, and in many saline springs. It occurs also in the mineral
bromyrite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bromism</ent>⟦br⟧
